## **CSS Layout Guide – Four‑Step Model Web Page**
*(mirrors Letter/A4 proportions at typical laptop viewport ≈ 960 px wide)*

```css
/* Base structure */
body {
  font-family: "Open Sans", Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 0;
  background: #ffffff;
  color: #333;
}

.wrapper {
  width: 960px;           /* equivalent to 8.5 in */
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding-bottom: 60px;
}

/* Header / Branding bar  */
header {
  height: 144px;          /* ≈ 1.5 in (96 px per inch at screen density) */
  background: linear-gradient(to right,
    #2A6EBB 20%, #3EA86B 40%, #E58A25 60%, #A0A0A0 80%);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 0 24px;
}
header .logo {
  height: 72px;
}
header .resources {
  font-size: 0.9em;
  color: #fff;
}

/* Four step bands */
section.step {
  height: 192px;          /* ≈ 2 in each band */
  padding: 24px 48px;
  margin: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}
.step:nth-child(1) { background-color: rgba(42,110,187,0.2); }
.step:nth-child(2) { background-color: rgba(62,168,107,0.2); }
.step:nth-child(3) { background-color: rgba(229,138,37,0.2); }
.step:nth-child(4) { background-color: rgba(160,160,160,0.2); }

.step h2 {
  flex: 0 0 200px;
  font-size: 22px;
}
.step p {
  flex: 1;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 1.4;
}

/* Footer / QR / grounding tip */
footer {
  height: 96px;           /* ≈ 1 in */
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 0 48px;
  font-size: 12px;
  border-top: 2px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}
footer .grounding {
  font-style: italic;
}
```

**HTML structure**

```html
<div class="wrapper">
  <header>
    <img src="logo.png" class="logo" alt="Program Logo">
    <div class="resources">Support is always available – Call or text 988 | findahelpline.com</div>
  </header>

  <section class="step">
    <h2>1 · Acknowledge Emotion</h2>
    <p>Listen first. Name the feeling you hear. Example: “It sounds like you’re overwhelmed.”</p>
  </section>

  <section class="step">
    <h2>2 · Ground in Present</h2>
    <p>Use one small physical anchor – breath or sensory detail. Example: “Can you notice one thing around you?”</p>
  </section>

  <section class="step">
    <h2>3 · Shift Toward Safety & Help</h2>
    <p>Collaborate on next step. Example: “Let’s reach someone who can help right now.”</p>
  </section>

  <section class="step">
    <h2>4 · Set Boundaries & Handoff</h2>
    <p>Warm closure + next support. Example: “I care about you and want you to talk with a counselor next.”</p>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <div class="grounding">Breathe out longer than in · Notice one color · Stretch before next conversation.</div>
    <img src="qr.png" width="60" height="60" alt="findahelpline QR">
  </footer>
</div>
```

---

**Designer tips**
- Keep background tints subtle for readability.  
- Test responsiveness: scale each band’s height proportionally for mobiles.  
- Replace text with localized helpline information if page used internationally.  

