## **Responsive CSS Addition**

```css
/* --- Responsive adjustments for tablets & phones --- */

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .wrapper {
    width: 100%;
  }

  header {
    flex-direction: column;
    height: auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  header .logo {
    height: 56px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  header .resources {
    padding-bottom: 8px;
  }

  section.step {
    flex-direction: column;
    height: auto;
    padding: 16px 24px;
  }

  .step h2 {
    flex: none;
    width: 100%;
    font-size: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .step p {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    text-align: center;
  }

  footer {
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    height: auto;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 16px;
  }

  footer .grounding {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
}

/* Optional micro‑animation for each band appear on scroll */
.step {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(20px);
  transition: all 0.4s ease;
}
.step.visible {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateY(0);
}
```

**Quick JS helper (optional):**

```html
<script>
window.addEventListener("scroll", () => {
  document.querySelectorAll(".step").forEach((el) => {
    const rect = el.getBoundingClientRect();
    if (rect.top < window.innerHeight - 100) el.classList.add("visible");
  });
});
</script>
```

**Result**
- On screens under 768 px wide, each colored band stacks vertically with centered text.  
- The scroll animation fades them in one by one for clarity without heavy scripting.  
- You can adjust breakpoints (e.g., 600 px / 480 px) to taste.

